For production:
# bin/kc.sh start --optimized    (for debug)

### 1. Build the Optimized Image
Run this command once to "lock in" your database and hostname settings:

  cd /opt/keycloak
  bin/kc.sh build` 

---

### 2. Create a Dedicated User (Security Best Practice)

Running Keycloak as `root` is a security risk. Create a system user that owns the Keycloak files:

  sudo groupadd -r keycloak
  sudo useradd -r -g keycloak -d /opt/keycloak -s /sbin/nologin keycloak
  sudo chown -R keycloak:keycloak /opt/keycloak

---

### 3. Create the Systemd Service File

Create the file at '/etc/systemd/system/keycloak.service':

[Unit]
Description=Keycloak Identity Management
After=network.target mariadb.service
# If MariaDB is on a different node, remove mariadb.service from After

[Service]
Type=simple
User=keycloak
Group=keycloak
WorkingDirectory=/opt/keycloak
# Optimized start uses the settings from the 'build' command
ExecStart=/opt/keycloak/bin/kc.sh start --optimized
Restart=always
RestartSec=10
LimitNOFILE=65536

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target`

---

### 4. Enable and Start

Run the following commands to register and launch the service:

sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable keycloak
sudo systemctl start keycloak

### 5. Verify the Status

Check if the service is running and look for any Java/Quarkus errors in the logs:

  systemctl status keycloak

# To see live logs:
  journalctl -u keycloak -f`
